# Cursor Rules for SPH Website

## Content Guidelines

### Text Formatting
- **NEVER use em dashes (—) or en dashes (–)** - Always use single hyphens (-) instead
- **NEVER use special Unicode dashes** - These are AI content indicators
- Use standard ASCII characters only for dashes and punctuation
- Maintain consistent formatting across all pages

### Writing Style
- Use clear, professional language
- Avoid overly complex sentence structures
- Keep paragraphs concise and readable
- Use active voice when possible

## Code Standards

### React/Next.js
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Follow Next.js 14+ App Router conventions
- Use proper component naming (PascalCase)
- Implement proper error boundaries

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use semantic HTML elements

### File Organization
- Keep components in `/src/components/`
- Page components in `/src/app/[page]/`
- Use proper imports and exports
- Maintain clean file structure

## Content Management

### CTAs (Call-to-Actions)
- Standardize all CTAs to "Learn More" linking to `/contact`
- Maintain consistent button styling across pages
- Use clear, action-oriented language

### Images and Assets
- Use WebP format for images when possible
- Optimize images for web performance
- Use descriptive alt text for accessibility

## Quality Assurance

### Before Committing
- Check for em dashes or en dashes in all text content
- Verify all CTAs follow the "Learn More" standard
- Test responsive design on multiple screen sizes
- Ensure all links work correctly

### Code Review Checklist
- No special Unicode characters in text content
- Consistent styling and formatting
- Proper TypeScript types
- Clean, readable code structure
